German Cities in 1600:

More than 40.000 inhabitants – Hamburg, Cologne, Nuremberg, Augsburg.

20.000 – 40.000 inhabitants – Lubeck, Bremen, Magdeburg, Lepzig, Breslau, Frankfurt, Ulm, Regensburg, Strasburg, Vienna.

10.000 – 20.000 inhabitants – Stralsund, Rostock, Luneburg, Halberstadt, Brandenburg, Frankfurt (Oder), Erfurt, Bamberg, Aschen, Stuugart, Munich.
